<span id="freeTextContainer10970559285671585996">It has been many years since I last read any of Carl Sagan&apos;s books. This book was a delightful surprise. Easy to read, very thoughtful, and quite entertaining. In a nutshell, Sagan does not come out and say &quot;there is no god.&quot; Instead, he simply says that there is no physical evidence for the existence of a god. </span>
  <span id="freeText10970559285671585996" style="display:none">It has been many years since I last read any of Carl Sagan's books. This book was a delightful surprise. Easy to read, very thoughtful, and quite entertaining. In a nutshell, Sagan does not come out and say "there is no god." Instead, he simply says that there is no physical evidence for the existence of a god. </span>
